label.value: Posterior papillary muscle of left ventricle

definition.value: Papillary muscle of left ventricle which has as its parts the posteromedial and anterior heads of the posterior papillary muscle of left ventricle and is continuous with the inferior wall of left ventricle..

label.value: Posteromedial head of posterior papillary muscle of left ventricle

definition.value: Region of posterior papillary muscle of left ventricle which is attached to the posterior commissural leaflet of mitral valve through the chorda tendinea of left ventricle.
